<HEADLINE>
FT  23 JUN 93 / UK Company News: Shake-up at the Vestey empire
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROLAND RUDD
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
LORD VESTEY has taken some of his executives by surprise by deciding to
establish a new management structure for the Vestey Group under which all
group operations and investments will report.
Lord Vestey and Mr Edmund Vestey, who is chairman of the Western United
Investment Company, are looking to hire a new chief executive and chief
financial officer responsible for 'all the family interests'.
However, Mr Terry Robinson, chief executive of Union International, the
principal trading arm of the Vestey Group, has privately made it clear that
he is not prepared in the short-term to report to any new management
company.
One of Union International's advisers yesterday said: 'Mr Robinson does not
currently report to anyone, not even Union's holding company Western United.
His contract, which has another 18 months to run, mentions nothing about
reporting to any new Vestey company'.
The Vesteys recruited Mr Robinson from Lonrho, the international trading
conglomerate, to turn around the heavily-indebted Union International. The
company recently reported profit before tax and exceptional items of Pounds
30.8m in the year ended December 31, compared with a loss of Pounds 20.5m in
the previous year.
Mr Robinson reached a standstill agreement with Union's banks last year. The
arrangement, however, is unlikely to be completed until December 1994.
Mr Robinson is understood to have told the Vestey family that he is more
than happy with reporting to a new management company, but only after
Union's restructuring is completed by the end of next year.
He yesterday confined himself to saying: 'I welcome the idea of experienced
management at the top of the Vestey empire'.
Mr Edmund Vestey said: 'It is in the best interests of all the group's
stakeholders - employers, customers, shareholders - for a professional
management team to be given strategic and day-to-day management control.'
Mr Vestey will become non-executive chairman of the company and three other
representatives of the family will be non-executive directors.
</TEXT>
