<HEADLINE>
FT  23 JUN 93 / Observer: Small world
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Meanwhile London Business School's long hunt for its first professor and
assistant professor in business ethics has at last been resolved, but only
after some embarrassment for the selectors.
The problem seems to have been a dearth of ethical academics. In its
eagerness to draw on the best expertise in compiling the shortlist, the
committee originally recruited the highly-respected Jesuit Jack Mahoney as
external adviser. It then realised that the vital missing name was Mahoney
himself, who - whilst not involved in his own selection in any way -
yesterday became the anointed one for the professorship.
</TEXT>
