FT  23 JUN 93 / Parliament and Politics: Heseltine set for lengthy absence
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MICHAEL CASSELL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MR MICHAEL Heseltine, trade and industry secretary, is unlikely to resume
ministerial responsibilities until late summer, Michael Cassell writes.
Mr Heseltine, who suffered a mild heart attack on Monday, is recovering in
hospital in Venice, where doctors yesterday were satisfied with his
progress. He is expected to remain there for a few days before being given
medical permission to be flown home.
In spite of Mr Heseltine's central role in Mr John Major's government it is
expected that he will not return to Westminster before the summer recess in
late July.
He would then be able to extend his period of recuperation well into the
holidays, with the possibility that he could re-emerge on the political
scene at the Tory party conference in early October.
