FT  23 JUN 93 / Parliament and Politics: Rifkind rejects UN combat role
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
UN FORCES should not be made to adopt a combat role in Bosnia, Mr Malcolm
Rifkind, the defence secretary, insisted yesterday.
He was responding to suggestions the rules of engagement for British troops
in UN humanitarian operations might have to be changed to allow for the task
of protecting civilians.
He said: 'We do not believe that the current rules of engagement need to be
changed in order to assist nations in their humanitarian efforts. Clearly if
any new mandate was to be considered, it would open the question as to
whether the rules were appropriate.'
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>BAZ  Bosnia-Hercegovina, East Europe.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
