<HEADLINE>
FT  23 JUN 93 / 2% limit on water bill rises urged
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
OFWAT, the water industry regulator, yesterday called for rises in water
bills to be held to about 2 per cent a year in line with likely rises in
household income.
Mr Ian Byatt, Ofwat's director-general, said: 'Escalating price increases
must stop.' He added: 'A continuing increase in prices, well above the rate
of inflation, will not be acceptable to customers.'
Ofwat's report for the year to March, published yesterday, showed that
customer complaints to its regional committees rose by 39 per cent last year
to 14,795. Of these, 62 per cent were about rising prices and other problems
with bills.
The sharp annual rises in bills are being caused by the industry's
modernisation, costing about Pounds 45bn, which is required by new UK and
European environmental rules.
