Portugal in 1995.
Two loans totalling Es17bn will be used to finance small and medium-sized
companies in industry, industrial services and tourism. Two other loans of
Es6bn each will finance roads. Among other loans, one of Es5.7bn will be
used to improve energy facilities on the Azores islands.
The loans bring total EIB lending to Portugal in 1993 to Es137bn. But other
approved projects are expected to lift the total to Es330bn.
