<DATELINE>
   MELBOURNE
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Australia is to lodge a complaint with Gatt over Canadian moves to impose a
25 per cent tariff on Australian beef imports, Emilia Tagaza writes from
Melbourne.
The tariff, which will be in effect for the rest of 1993, was imposed after
the Canadian International Trade Tribunal found there was a potential threat
