FT  22 JUN 93 / French seen as more protectionist
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Gloomy about prospects for an end to the recession, most French people
favour protectionism on imports and a tough line with the US on world trade
negotiations, according to an opinion poll released yesterday, Reuter
reports from Paris. Some 67 per cent thought France and Europe should limit
non-French or non-European imports and 62 per cent thought Europe should be
tougher with Washington in the Gatt world trade talks, even if this meant
upsetting relations with the US. The poll by CSA for Le Parisien newspaper
also said 79 per cent of those asked thought the recession would go on for
at least a year or two.
